  "text": "There are important limitations of the current study. First, the study population consists largely of white male participants. Sex and race were controlled for in analyses, but fibrinolytic markers may differ by sex and race [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and further studies will be needed to determine whether the effects of tesamorelin differ according to sex or race. Second, many inflammatory markers show substantial intraindividual variance, which may reduce our ability to characterize changes in these markers over time. In addition, there is a possibility of type I error.",
